ME: I want to use the wttr.in API directly (e.g., https://wttr.in/Perth?format=j1) and return JSON weather data. Iâ€™m a beginner, so please explain each step clearly. 

AI: 
Sure! The steps are: 
Use the requests library to call the API. 
Parse the JSON response. 
Extract useful fields (current condition, forecast dates, temperature, precipitation). 
Return a clean dictionary so other parts of your program (charts, responses) can use it easily. 
Hereâ€™s a first version: 
import requests  
def get_weather_data(location, forecast_days=5): 
    url = f"https://wttr.in/{location}?format=j1" 
    r = requests.get(url) 
    data = r.json() 
    return data 

 

